  "id": "",
  "summary": "Heavily obfuscated code shipped under hidden.ad/ directory",
  "details": "The package ships dozens of heavily obfuscated JavaScript files (hexadecimal-prefixed identifiers like _0x407389, _0xfcd730, etc.) inside a hidden `.ad/` directory, including files with suggestive names such as `phone-validator.js`, `sms-providers.js`, `smtp-health-cache.js`, `web-command.js`, `from-generator.js`, and a series of single-letter/two-letter named files `x0.js` through `xz.js`. The pervasive use of obfuscation across the package's code surface obscures the actual behavior and makes intent unverifiable from inspection alone. File names suggesting SMS/SMTP/phone validator/web-command tooling combined with intentional obfuscation are concerning for an abuse-tooling distribution pattern, but contextual tracing of the runtime behavior did not produce conclusive evidence of installer-side data exfiltration, RCE, dropper, or silent-relay in this analysis. Recommend human review of the deobfuscated contents and the package's declared purpose before allowing into a build.",
